John Young, 66, and his wife Elaine, 54, were sitting in the front room of their home in Oldham, Greater Manchester, when thugs began pelting their front door with stones .
Mr Young, who served with the Royal Electrical and Mechanical Engineers during the Irish troubles, was hit in the left eye by the brick .
He suffered an open wound to his forehead and was taken to hospital .
Police have launched an investigation but say there appears to be no motive .